A GROUP of high school pupils have starred in their own cover of music video Uptown Funk.
Williamwood High in Clarkston, Renfrewshire was transformed as the staff and pupils got their funk on to film their alternative take on the hit song by Mark Ronson featuring Bruno Mars.
The video was shown at the graduation ceremony, the final event of their six years at the school.
In another Scottish school, pupils and teachers also made their own hilarious music video. 
 
